<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-816-038  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 816 038.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  August 27, 1990 v5 n109 p7(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Satellite transmission: Romania chooses California Microwave'ssystems. (Satellite Transmission Systems Inc. negotiates withRomanian government for the supply of a satellite earth station)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   California Microwave Inc. (contracts)Satellite Transmission Systems Inc. (contracts).andO;Topic:     Satellite CommunicationsSubsidiary CompaniesNegotiationGovernment ContractsEastern EuropeRomania.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SATELLITE TRANSMISSION: ROMANIA CHOOSES CALIFORNIA MICROWAVE'S  SYSTEMSandM;California Microwave Inc. announced that its subsidiary, SatelliteTransmission Systems Inc. (STS) has been chosen to negotiate with theMinistry of Communications of Romania to supply a major satellite earthstation to be located near Bucharest, Romania.andM;Romania is one of the first Eastern Bloc countries to be admitted to theEuropean regional satellite consortium, EUTELSAT, and would be the first tocontract for EUTELSAT earth station facilities.andM;It is presently anticipated that the satellite earth station would becompleted in the first half of 1991, providing Romania with the capabilityfor direct voice, data and facsimile communications with all major WesternEuropean countries.andM;The selection of STS to negotiate the contract, estimated to be in excess of$3 million, was made on the basis of competitive bids from majorinternational suppliers.andP;  Nissho Iwai, a large Japanese trading company, isacting as intermediary to provide financing for the project.andM;CONTRANSIMEX is the Romanian national import/export entity responsible forthe procurement of the satellite earth station.andM;STS, located in Hauppauge, NY, designs and constructs communicationssatellite terminals, equipment and networks for EUTELSAT, INTELSAT anddomestic satellite applications, and has built and installed over 600 majorearth stations worldwide.andO;</TEXT></DOC>